INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (94,'199600103009','i) $$f:x \\mapsto (x-1)^2$$;From the graph, the range of values of f(x) is $$0\\leq f(x)\\leq 16$$ (ANS);img; ii) $$f^2(x)=(f(x)-1)^2$$;since $$0\\leq f(x)\\leq 16$$,;$$0\\leq (f(x)-1)^2\\leq (16-1)^2$$;$$0\\leq f(x)^2\\leq 225$$(ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (95,'199600103010','img;i) The equation $$\\tan x=\\cos x$$ has two roots in the range $$0^{\\circ}$$ to $$360^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);ii) From the graph, tan  x and cos  x are both increasing as x increases in the interval from $$180^{\\circ}$$ to $$270^{\\circ}$$. ;Therefore $$180^{\\circ}<x<270^{\\circ}$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (96,'199600103011','a) $$(1+2x)(3+x)^11$$;= $$(1+2x)(...+((11),(8))3^3x^8+((11),(9))3^2x^9+...)$$;= $$(1+2x)(...+4455x^8+495x^9+...)$$;= $$...+(495+2 \\times 4455)x^9+...$$;= $$...+9405x^9+...$$;Therefore the coefficient of $$x^9$$ is 9405. (ANS);b) $$(x^2- \\frac{ 2}{x})^7 ;= ...+(\\binom{7}{r}(x^2)^{7-r}( \\frac{ (-2)}{x})^r+...$$; =$$...+(\\binom{7}{x})(x)^{14-3r}(-2)^r+...$$;	Let $$14-3r=5$$;$$3r=9$$;$$r=3$$;Therefore coefficient of $$x^3=(\\binom{7}{3}(-2)^3=-280$$ (ANS);c) $$(a+b)^n=a^n+na^{n-1}b+ \\frac{ (n(n-1))}{2}a^{n-2}b^2+...$$;Therefore $$p=a^n, q=na^{n-1}b, r= \\frac{ (n(n-1))}{2}a^{n-2}b^2$$;$$ \\frac{ q^2}{(pr)}= \\frac{ (n^{2a^{(2n-2)}}b^2)}{(a^n(\\frac{ (n(n-1))}{2}a^{(n-2)}b^2))}$$; =$$ \\frac{ (n^2a^{(2n-2)}b^2)}{( \\frac{ (n(n-1))}{2}a^{(2n-2)}b^2)}$$;= $$ \\frac{ (2n)}{(n-1)}$$ (SHOWN);Given that p = 4, q = 32 and r = 96,;$$ \\frac{ (2n)}{(n-1) }= \\frac{ (32)^2}{(4(96))}= \\frac{ 8}{3}$$;$$6n=8n-8$$;$$2n=8$$;$$n=4$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (97,'199600103012','img;a) To find b:;$$-\\frac{1}{2}x+5=x-1$$;$$\\frac{3}{2}x=6$$;$$x=4$$;Therefore $$b=4$$;To find a: ; $$-\\frac{1}{2}x+5=1-x$$;$$\\frac{1}{2}x=-4$$;$$x=-8$$;Therefore $$a=-8$$;When x = 4, $$y=-\\frac{1}{2}x+5=3$$;Therefore B(4, 3);When x = - 8, $$y=-\\frac{1}{2}x+5=9$$;Therefore A(-8, 9);distance AB = $$\\sqrt{(4-(-8))^2 +(3-9)^2}$$;=$$\\sqrt{144+36}$$;=$$\\sqrt{180}$$;=$$6\\sqrt5$$ (ANS); b)i)$$gh(x)=g(\\frac{1}{2}(4x+3))$$;  =$$ \\frac{ 2}{(4x+3)}$$ (ANS); ii)$$hg(x)=h(\\frac{1}{x})$$;=$$\\frac{1}{2}( \\frac{ 4}{x+3})$$ (ANS); iii)hg(x) = gh(x);$$\\frac{1}{2}( \\frac{ 4}{x+3})= \\frac{ 2}{(4x+3)}$$;$$ \\frac{ (4+3x)}{x}= \\frac{ 4}{(4x+3)}$$;$$(4x+3)(4x+3)=4x$$;$$12x^2+25x+12=4x$$;$$12x^2+21x+12=0$$;$$4x^2+7x+4=0$$;Discriminant = $$7^2-4(4)(4)=49-64$$=$$-15<0$$	Therefore the equation of $$4x^2+7x+4=0$$ has no solutions. Hence gh(x) = hg(x) has no solutions. (SHOWN)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (98,'199600103013','a) i) since $$0^{\\circ}\\leq x\\leq 360^{\\circ}$$;we have $$0^{\\circ}\\leq 2x\\leq 720^{\\circ}$$;$$2\\cot 2x = 5$$;$$\\cot 2x=\\frac{5}{2}$$;$$\\tan 2x=\\frac{2}{5}$$;$$2x=21.8^{\\circ},201.8^{\\circ},381.8^{\\circ},561.8^{\\circ}$$;$$x=10.9^{\\circ},100.9^{\\circ},190.9^{\\circ},280.9^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);ii)$$3\\sin y\\tan y+8=0$$;$$3\\sin y \\frac{\\sin y}{\\cos y}+8=0$$;$$3 \\frac{ (\\sin ^2y)}{\\cos y} +8=0$$;$$3 \\frac{ (1-\\cos ^2y)}{\\cos y}+8=0$$;$$3-3\\cos ^2y+8\\cos y=0$$;$$3\\cos ^2y-8\\cos y-3=0$$;$$(3\\cos y+1)(\\cos y-3)=0$$;Therefore; $$\\cos y=-\\frac{1}{3}$$;$$y=109.5^{\\circ},250.5^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);b)$$ \\frac{(2-\\csc^{2}A)}{(\\csc^{2}A+2\\cot A)}= \\frac{ (2- \\frac{1}{(\\sin ^2A)})}{( \\frac{1}{(\\sin ^2A)}+ \\frac{(2\\cos A)}{(\\sin A)})}$$;= $$ \\frac{ (2\\sin ^2A-1)}{(1+2\\sin A\\cos A)}$$;= $$ \\frac{ (2\\sin ^2A-(\\sin ^2A+\\cos ^2A))}{(\\sin ^2A+\\cos ^2A+2\\sin A\\cos A)}$$;= $$ \\frac{ (\\sin ^2A-\\cos ^2A)}{(\\sin A+\\cos A)^2}$$;= $$ \\frac{ ((\\sin A+\\cos A)(\\sin A-\\cos A))}{(\\sin A+\\cos A)^2}$$;= $$ \\frac{ (\\sin A-\\cos A)}{(\\sin A+\\cos A)}$$ (SHOWN)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (99,'199600103014','i) $$\\vec{OA} \\ast \\vec{OB}=|\\vec{OA}||\\vec{OB}|\\cos  \\angle AOB$$;$$(\\binom{10}{5})(\\binom{1}{3})=\\sqrt{10^2+5^2}\\ast \\sqrt{1^2+3^2}\\cos  \\angle AOB$$;$$10+15 = \\sqrt{125} \\sqrt{10} \\cos  \\angle AOB$$;$$\\cos  \\angle AOB = \\frac{ 25}{\\sqrt{1250}} = \\frac{ 25}{(25\\sqrt2)} = \\frac{ 1}{\\sqrt2}$$;$$\\angle AOB = 45^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);ii)$$\\vec{AB}=\\vec{OB}-\\vec{OA}$$;=$$(\\binom{1}{3})-(\\binom{10}{5})=(\\binom{-9}{-2})$$;$$|\\vec{AB}|=\\sqrt{9^2+2^2}$$;=$$\\sqrt{85}$$ (ANS);$$\\vec{AC}=\\vec{OC}-\\vec{OA}$$;=$$(\\binom{c}{3c})-(\\binom{10}{5})=(\\binom{c-10}{3c-5})$$;$$|\\vec{AC}|=\\sqrt{(c-10)^2+(3c-5)^2}$$;since $$|\\vec{AC}|= |\\vec{AB}|$$;we have;$$\\sqrt{(c-10)^2+(3c-5)^2}=\\sqrt{85}$$;$$(c-10)^2+(3c-5)^2=85$$;$$c^2-20c+100+9c^2-30c+25=85$$;$$10c^2-50c+40=0$$;$$c^2-5c+4=0$$;$$(c-4)(c-1)=0$$;Therefore c = 4 or 1;since c > 1, therefore c = 4 (ANS);since $$ \\angle BAD=90^{\\circ}$$, then $$\\vec{AB} \\ast \\vec{AD}=0$$;	since is on OB produced,;$$\\vec{OD}=\\lambda  \\vec{OB}, \\lambda >1$$;=$$((\\lambda ),(3\\lambda ))$$;$$\\vec{AD}=\\vec{OD}-\\vec{OA}$$;=$$(\\binom{\\lambda -10}{3\\lambda -5})$$;$$\\vec{AB} \\ast \\vec{AD}=0$$;$$(\\binom{-9}{-2}) \\ast (\\binom{\\lambda -10}{3\\lambda -5})=0$$;$$-9\\lambda +90-6\\lambda +10=0$$;$$15\\lambda =100$$;$$\\lambda = \\frac{ 20}{3}$$;Therefore $$\\vec{OD}=(\\binom{\\frac{20}{3z}}{20})$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (100,'199600103015','i) $$\\angle PQR=60^{\\circ}$$	;Therefore;$$\\angle DQF = 360^{\\circ}-90^{\\circ}-90^{\\circ}-\\angle PQR$$;=$$120^{\\circ}$$;And $$\\angle QPS = 120^{\\circ}$$;Therefore;$$\\angle CPA=360^{\\circ}-90^{\\circ}-90^{\\circ}-\\angle QPS$$;=$$60^{\\circ}$$;area of QDEF = $$\\frac{120}{360}\\pi r^2=\\frac{1}{3}\\pi 30^2=300\\pi cm^2$$;area of PABC = $$\\frac{60}{360}\\pi r^2=\\frac{1}{6}\\pi 30^2=150\\pi cm^2$$;Total area = 4 x area of CDQP + 2 x area of QDEF +2 x area of PABC; = 4(30 x 80) + 2(300p) + 2(150 p); = 9600 + 900 p; = $$12400cm^2$$ (3sf) (ANS);ii) arc length DEF = $$\\frac{120}{360}(2\\pi r)$$; =$$\\frac{2}{3}\\pi (30)$$; =$$20\\pi cm$$;arc length ABC = $$\\frac{60}{360}(2\\pi r)$$; =$$\\frac{1}{3}\\pi (30)$$; =$$10\\pi cm$$;Length of external boundary;= (4 x CD) + (2 x arc length DEF) + (2 x arc length ABC);= 4 x 80 + 2 x 20p + 2 x 10p;= 320 + 60 p;$$\\approx 508cm$$ (3sf) (ANS);img; $$\\angle CPY = 90^{\\circ}$$;$$\\angle DQX = 90^{\\circ}$$;$$\\angle CPY + \\angle APY = 90^{\\circ}$$;and since DQ is perpendicular to QX; $$60^{\\circ}+\\angle APY=90^{\\circ}$$;$$\\angle APY = 30^{\\circ}$$;area of triangle APY;=$$\\frac{1}{2} \\times AP \\times AY$$;=$$\\frac{1}{2}(30)(30\\tan 30^{\\circ})$$;=$$\\frac{450}{\\sqrt3}$$;=$$150\\sqrt3cm^2$$;area of QDEX = $$\\frac{1}{4}\\pi r^2$$;=$$\\frac{1}{4}\\pi (30)^2$$;=$$225\\pi cm^2$$;area of smaller part;= area of triangle APY + area of QDEX;= $$150\\sqrt3+150\\pi +2400+225\\pi $$;=$$2400+375\\pi +150\\sqrt3$$;$$\\approx 3840cm^2$$ (3sf) (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (101,'199600103016','i) $$v=0.75t-0.03t^2$$;acceleration, ;$$a=\\frac{\\mathrm{d} v}{\\mathrm{d} t} $$;=$$0.75-0.06t$$;when a = 0, ;0.75 - 0.06t = 0;t = 12.5 s (ANS);ii) displacement, s = $$\\int v dt$$;distance,;$$s=\\int_0^25vdt$$;=$$\\int_0^250.75t-0.03t^2dt$$;=$$[0.375t^2-0.01t^3]_0^25$$;=$$78.125m$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (102,'199600103017','i)$$V = 2(x+4)^2-32$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} t}=4(x+4)$$;Now,;$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} t}=\\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} x} \\ast \\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;$$50=4(x+4)\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;when x = 16 ,;$$50=4(16+4)\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}=0.625$$;therefore the rate of increase of the depth of the liquid is $$0.625cms^{-1}$$;ii)	$$50=4(x+4)\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;When $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}=0.8$$,;$$50=4(x+4)(0.8)$$;x = 11.625 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (103,'199600103018','Depth = 2x;Width = 40 - 4x ;Length = $$\\frac{ (62.5-5x)}{2}$$ therefore;Volume = $$2x(40-4x)( \\frac{ (62.5-5x)}{2})$$;=$$x(20x^2-450x+2500)$$;=$$10x(2x^2-45x+250)$$;= $$10(2x^3-45x^2+250x)$$ (SHOWN) ;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x}(2x^3-45x^2+250x)$$;=$$6x^2-90x+250$$;At the stationary points,;$$6x^2-90x+250=0$$;$$3x^2-45x+125=0$$;$$x=\\frac{ (45 \\pm  \\sqrt{45^2-4(3)(125)})}{6}$$;=$$\\frac{ (45 \\pm  \\sqrt(525))}{6}$$;= 11.3 or 3.68;If x = 11.3, then;depth = 22.6;width = -5.2 < 0 (impossible);length = 3.0;If x = 3.68, then;depth = 7.36;width = 25.28;length = 22.05;Therefore x = 3.68 (ANS);volume = 7.36x25.28x22.05;   = $$4100cm^3$$ (ANS); $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} x} =10(6x^2-90x+250)$$;$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d}^{2} V}{\\mathrm{d} x^{2}}=10(12x-90)$$;When x = 3.68,; $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d}^{2} V}{\\mathrm{d} x^{2}}=10(12(3.68)-90) <0$$;Therefore the value of V when x = 3.68 is a maximum value. (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (104,'199600104001','(a) Let $$f(x)=ax^3+x^2+bx$$ 	By remainder theorem,;$$f(-1)=3$$;$$-a+1-b=3$$;$$a+b=-2$$ ……(1);and;$$f(2)=6$$;$$8a+4+2b=6$$;$$4a+b=1 ……(2)$$;Solving (1) and (2) simultaneously, gives ;a = 1, b = - 3.;Therefore $$f(x)=x^3+x^2-3x$$,;The remainder when the expression id divided by x - 3 is,;$$f(x)=3^3+3^2-3(3)$$;  = 27 (ANS); b) Let $$g(x)=2x^3+7x^2-2x-1$$;By trial and error, we found that;$$g(\\frac{1}{2})=\\frac{1}{4}+\\frac{7}{4}-1-1=0$$;By factor theorem, (2x - 1) is a factor of g(x).;$$g(x)=2x^3+7x^2-2x-1$$;=$$(2x-1)(x^2+4x+1)$$;For g(x) = 0;$$(2x-1)(x^2+4x+1)=0$$;$$x=\\frac{1}{2}$$;or $$x=\\frac{ (-4\\pm \\sqrt(16-4))}{2}$$;=$$-0.27 or -3.73$$;The answers are $$\\frac{1}{2},-0.27 and -3.73$$;img;(ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (105,'199600104002','i)$$y=(x^2-4)(2x-1)$$;when x = 0, y = (- 4)(- 1) = 4;therefore the curve cuts the y - axis at (0, 4);when y = 0,;$$(x^2-4)(2x-1)=0$$;$$x=\\pm 2 or \\frac{1}{2}$$;Therefore the curve cuts the x- axis at (-2, 0), $$(\\frac{1}{2},0)$$,(2,0) (ANS);ii) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 2(x^2-4)+2x(2x-1)$$;=$$2(x^2-4+2x^2-x)$$;=$$2(3x^2-x-4)$$;At the turning points,;$$3x^2-x-4=0$$;$$(3x-4)(x+1)=0$$;$$x=\\frac{4}{3} or -1$$;when $$x=\\frac{4}{3},y=(\\frac{16}{9}-4)( \\frac{8}{3}-1)=- \\frac{100}{27}$$;when x = -1, y = (1 -4 )(-2 - 1) = 9;Therefore the turning points are $$(\\frac{4}{3},-\\frac{100}{27}) and (-1,9)$$.');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (106,'199600104003','a) since;$$a+5d=5a$$;$$5d=4a$$ …..(1);$$a+(a+d)+(a+2d)+(a+3d)+(a+4d)+(a+5d)=36$$;$$6a+15d=36$$;$$2a+5d=12$$……(2);Sub. (1) into (2):; 2a + 4a = 12;a =2 ;Therefore ;$$d=\\frac{ (4a)}{5}$$;=$$\\frac{8}{5}$$;The lengths are : 2cm, 3.6 cm, 5.2 cm, 6.8cm,8.4cm,10cm (ANS);b) Let a =10 and r =1.2 where a is the first term and r is the common ratio of a G.P.;$$S_n=\\frac{ (a(r^n-1))}{(r-1)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ ((10(1.2^n-1))}{(1.2-1))}$$;=$$50(1.2^n-1)$$;Solve,;$$S_n>800$$;$$50(1.2^n-1)>800$$;$$1.2^n-1>16$$;$$1.2^n>17$$;$$n\\lg 1.2>\\lg 17$$;$$n>15.5$$;therefore 16 days are needed to complete the task. (ANS);c)  i) since $$S_1=T_1$$ therefore;First term, ;$$a=S_1$$;  =$$2(1)^2+1$$; = 3 (ANS);ii)$$T_1+T_2=S_2$$;$$3+T_2=2(2)^2+2$$;$$3+T_2=10$$;$$T_2=7$$;Therefore common difference, d =$$T_2-T_1$$;=7-3;=4 (ANS); iii) $$T_10$$ = a+ 9d = 3 + 9(4) = 39 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (107,'199600104004','a) $$py=q^x$$	;Sub. x = 1, y = - 12 :;$$-12p=q$$……(1);Sub. ;$$x=-2,y=\\frac{3}{16};\\frac{3}{16}p=q^{(-2)}$$ …… (2);$$ \\frac{ ((1))}{((2))}: \\frac{ (-12)}{(( \\frac{3}{16}))}=q^3$$;$$q^3=-64$$;q = -4 (ANS);Sub. into (1):; -12p = - 4; $$p=\\frac{1}{3}$$ (ANS);b)$$\\lg x + 2\\lg y = 3$$;$$\\lg xy^2=3$$;$$xy^2=10^3$$;$$xy^2=1000$$ ……(1);$$x^2y=125$$ ……..(2);$$y=\\frac{125}{x^2}$$;Sub. into (1):;$$x(\\frac{125}{x^2})^2=1000$$;$$\\frac{15625}{x^3}=1000$$;$$x^3=\\frac{15625}{1000}$$;$$x=\\frac{5}{2}$$;Sub. into (2):; $$y=125 \\div (\\frac{5}{2})^2 = 125 \\times \\frac{4}{25} $$;= 20 ;Therefore, $$x=\\frac{5}{2}$$, y=20 (ANS);c)i)$$y =2xe^{-1}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 2e^{-x} - 2xe^{-x}$$;=$$2e^{-x}(1-x)$$;When x = 1, ;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=0$$;Therefore y has a stationary value when x = 1. (SHOWN);img;img;ii)$$x+1=10xe^{-x}$$;$$\\frac{1}{5}x+\\frac{1}{5}=2xe^{-x}$$;Draw the line $$y=\\frac{1}{5}x+\\frac{1}{5}$$ on the same axes. The solutions are x = 0.125 and 1.875. (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (108,'199600104006','a) i) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x}(\\frac{ (2x+5)}{(1+3x)})= \\frac{ ((1+3x)(2)-(2x+5)(3))}{(1+3x)^2}$$;=$$\\frac{ (2+6x-6x-15)}{(1+3x)^2}$$;= $$-\\frac{13}{(1+3x)^2}$$ (ANS);b) $$2x^2+xy-3y^2=7$$;Differentiate both sides w.r.t x,;$$4x+x\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}+y-6y\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=0$$;$$(6y-x)\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=4x+y$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{ (4x+y)}{(6y-x)}$$;At the point(2, 1),;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{ (4(2)+1)}{(6(1)-2)}$$; = $$\\frac{9}{4}$$ (ANS);	i) Given that $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}=0.08$$;when x  = 2,;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}= \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}  \\ast  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;=$$\\frac{ (4x+y)}{(6y-x)} \\ast \\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;=$$\\frac{ (4(2)+1)}{(6(1)-2)} \\ast (0.08)$$;= 0.18 (ANS);ii) since $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}=0.18 >0$$,;y is increasing (ANS);c) $$y = \\tan (x + 1)$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=sec^2(x+1)$$;when x = 0, $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=sec^2(1)$$;Gradient of tangent = $$sec^2(1)$$;	Gradient of normal ;= $$\\frac{-1}{gradient of tangent}$$;=$$\\frac{-1}{(sec^2(1))}$$;=$$-\\cos ^2(1)$$;=- 0.29 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (109,'199600104007','a)  i) $$AB = 8\\sin \\theta$$;   $$ BC = (7 + 8)\\cos \\theta$$ ; = $$15\\cos \\theta$$ ;Therefore perimeter of ABCD,;$$P = 2(AB + BC)$$;   $$= 2(8\\sin \\theta  + 15\\cos \\theta )$$;  $$ =16\\sin \\theta  + 30\\cos \\theta $$ (shown) ;ii) Let$$P=R\\sin (\\theta +\\alpha )$$;$$16\\sin \\theta +30\\cos \\theta =R\\sin \\theta \\cos \\alpha  + R\\cos \\theta \\sin \\alpha $$;Therefore;$$R\\cos  \\alpha  = 16$$ ……(1);$$R\\sin  \\alpha  = 30$$……(2);$$(1)^2+(2)^2: R^2(\\cos ^2\\alpha  + \\sin ^2\\alpha )=16^2+30^2$$;$$R^2=1156$$;R = 34 (ANS);$$ \\frac{ ((2))}{((1))}:\\tan  \\alpha  = \\frac{ 30}{16}$$;$$\\alpha  = 61.9^{\\circ}$$(ANS);iii)  Therefore $$P=34\\sin (\\theta +61.9^{\\circ})$$;since the maximum value of a sine function is 1, the maximum value of P is 34.(ANS);Furthermore,;$$\\sin (\\theta +61.9^{\\circ})=1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\sin  \\theta  + 61.9^{\\circ} =90^{\\circ}$$;$$\\theta  = 28.1^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);iv) When P = 20,;$$20=34\\sin (\\theta +61.9^{\\circ})$$;$$\\sin (\\theta +61.9^{\\circ})=\\frac{ 10}{17}$$;$$\\theta +61.9^{\\circ} = 144.0^{\\circ} or 36.0^{\\circ} (N.A)$$;$$\\theta  = 82.1^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);b)i) $$\\tan ^2A =\\frac{ (\\sin ^2A)}{(\\cos ^2A)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (1-\\cos ^2A)}{(\\cos ^2A)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (1-p^2)}{p^2}$$ (ANS);ii) $$\\cos 2A=2\\cos ^2A-1$$;=$$2p^2-1$$ (ANS);iii) $$\\cos 3A = \\cos (2A+A)$$;=$$\\cos 2A\\cos A-\\sin 2A\\sin A$$;=$$(2p^2-1)p-2\\sin ^2A\\cos A$$;=$$(2p^2-1)p-2(1-\\cos ^2A)p$$;=$$(2p^2-1)p-2(1-p^2)p$$;=$$2p^3-p-2p+2p^3$$;= $$4p^3-3p$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (110,'199600104008','i) $$x=p^2+1 and y=p-2$$;$$x-4y=6$$;$$(p^2+1)-4(p-2)=6$$;$$p^2-4p+3=0$$ (ANS);ii)$$p^2-4p+3=0$$;$$(p-3)(p-1)=0$$;$$p=1 or p=3$$;When p = 1,;$$x=1^2+1=2$$;$$y=1-2=-1$$;When p = 3,;$$x=3^2+1=10$$;$$y=3-2=1$$;Therefore the coordinates of A and B are (2, -1) and (10, 1) (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (111,'199600104005','img;img;a) $$ay^2-bx^3=1$$;$$y^2=\\frac{ b}{ax^3}+\\frac{ 1}{a}$$;Therefore the gradient of the line is $$\\frac{ b}{a}$$;and the vertical intercept is $$\\frac{ 1}{a}$$;From the graph,$$ \\frac{ 1}{a}= 4$$;a = 0.25 (ANS);$$ \\frac{ b}{a}=\\frac{ 10}{20}$$;$$\\frac{ b}{0.25} = \\frac{1}{2}$$;B = 0.125 (ANS);$$y^2-x^3=1$$;$$y^2=x^3+1$$;Therefore on the same axes as the previous graph, the line $$y^2=x^3+1$$ has a gradient of 1 and a vertical intercept at 1.;From the graph, $$(x^2,y^2)=(6,7)$$;Therefore x = 1.82, y = 2.65 (ANS);b)$$y^2=px^q$$;$$\\lg  y^2 = \\lg  px^q$$;$$2\\lg y=\\lg p +q\\lg x$$;$$\\lg y=\\frac{ q}{2}\\lg x+\\frac{1}{2}\\lg p$$;When lg  y is plotted against lg  x, the gradient is $$\\frac{ q}{2}$$ and the vertical intercept is $$\\frac{1}{2} \\lg  p$$;Therefore $$\\frac{ q}{2}=-2 \\Rightarrow  q=-4$$;and ;$$\\frac{1}{2}\\lg p = 0.5 \\Rightarrow  \\lg  p =1$$;$$\\Rightarrow  p=10$$;Therefore, p=10, q=-4 (ANS);c) Equation of the line:;$$ \\frac{ (y^2-3)}{(xy-1)}= \\frac{ (11-3)}{(5-1)}$$;$$ \\frac{ (y^2-3)}{(xy-1)}=2$$;$$y^2-3=2xy-2$$;$$y^2=2xy+1$$;When y = 3, 9 = 6x +1;$$x=\\frac{ 4}{3}$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (112,'199600104009','i) $$x=t^2-2t \\Rightarrow  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}=2t-2$$;$$y=t^2+2t \\Rightarrow  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}=2t+2$$;Therefore;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}  \\ast  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} t}{\\mathrm{d} x}$$;=$$\\frac{ (2t+2)}{(2t-2)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (t+1)}{(t-1)}$$ (ANS); ii)Gradient,;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{1}{2}$$;$$\\frac{ (t+1)}{(t-1)}=\\frac{1}{2}$$;$$2t+2=t-1$$;$$t=-3$$;$$x=(-3)^2-2(-3)=9+6=15$$;$$y=(-3)^2+2(-3)=9-6=3$$;Equation of tangent:;$$ \\frac{ (y-3)}{(x-15)}=\\frac{1}{2}$$;$$2y-6=x-15$$;$$2y-x+9=0$$ (ANS);iii)since the tangent to the curve at this point is parallel to the y- axis, then $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}$$ is infinity.;Therefore $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{ (t+1)}{(t-1)}= \\infty$$;Hence,; $$t-1=0 \\Rightarrow  t=1$$;$$x^2=(1)^2-2(1)=-1$$;$$y=(1)^2+2(1)=3$$;Therefore the coordinates are (-1, 3) (ANS);iv)$$x=t^2-2t$$ ……(1);$$y=t^2+2t$$ ……(2);(1) + (2):;$$2t^2=x+y$$;$$t^2=\\frac{ (x+y)}{2}$$;Sub. into (1):;$$x=\\frac{ (x+y)}{2}-2t$$;$$2t=\\frac{ (y-x)}{2}$$;$$t=\\frac{ (y-x)}{4}$$;Squaring both sides,;$$t^2=(\\frac{(y-x)}{4})^2$$;$$\\frac{ (x+y)}{2}=(\\frac{ (y-x)}{4})^2$$;$$8(x+y)=(y-x)^2$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (113,'199600104010','a) $$\\int2\\cos 3x+3\\sin (\\frac{ x}{2})dx$$;=$$\\frac{2}{3}\\sin 3x-6\\cos (\\frac{ x}{2})+c$$ (ANS);b)$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = \\sqrt{2x+3}$$;$$y=\\int \\sqrt{2x+3} dx$$;=$$\\frac{2}{3}  \\ast  \\frac{((2x+3)^ {\\frac{3}{2}})}{2 }+c$$;=$$\\frac{1}{3}(2x+3)^{\\frac{3}{2}}+c$$;Given that the curve passes through (3, 5),;$$5=\\frac{1}{3}(6+3)^{\\frac{3}{2}}+c$$;=$$9+c$$;$$c=-4$$;Therefore $$y=\\frac{1}{3}(2x+3)^{\\frac{3}{2}}-4$$ (ANS)	c)i) area = $$\\int_0^2ydx$$;=$$\\int_0^2 \\frac{ 4}{(3-x)}dx$$;=$$[-4\\ln (3-x)]_0^2$$;=$$-4\\ln 1+4\\ln 3$$;=$$4.39units^2$$ (ANS);ii)Volume = $$\\pi \\int_0^2y^2dx$$;=$$\\pi  \\int_0^2 \\frac{ 16}{((3-x)^2)}dx$$;=$$[\\frac{ (16\\pi )}{(3-x)}]_0^2$$;=$$16\\pi -\\frac{ (16\\pi )}{3}$$;= $$\\frac{ (32\\pi )}{3} units^3$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (114,'199700101001','$$y=x^2+5x-3$$ ……(1);$$2y=3x-2$$ ……(2);Subst (1) into (2), yield,;$$2(x^2+5x-3) = 3(x^2+5x-3)-2$$;$$2x^2+7x-4=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (2x-1)(x+4)=0$$;Therefore $$x=\\frac{1}{2}, x=-4$$ when $$x=\\frac{1}{2}$$,;(2) gives;$$y=\\frac{1}{2}[3(\\frac{1}{2})-2]=-\\frac{1}{4}$$;x = - 4, (2) gives ;$$y=\\frac{1}{2}[3(-4)-2]=-7$$;Hence the sets of values of x and y are ;$$(x,y)-=(\\frac{1}{2},-\\frac{1}{4})$$ or $$(x,y)-=(-4,-7)$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (115,'199700101002','a) For line AB,;gradient of line AB = $$\\frac{ (11-1)}{(3-(-2))}= \\frac{10}{5}=2$$;	using $$y=mx+c \\Rightarrow  y=2x+c$$;use point  A(-2, 1);$$1=2(-2)+c \\Rightarrow  c=5$$;therefore, y = 2x + 5 is the equation of line AB (ANS);For line CN,;gradient of line CN = $$-\\frac{1}{2}$$;use $$y=mx+c \\Rightarrow  y=-\\frac{1}{2}x+c$$;use point  c(-1, 8);$$8=-\\frac{1}{2}(-1)+c \\Rightarrow  c=\\frac{15}{2}$$;therefore, $$y=-\\frac{1}{2}x+\\frac{15}{2}$$ is the equation of CN (ANS);b) To find coordinates of N, solve for x and y from;$$y=2x+5$$ ……(1);$$y=-\\frac{1}{2}x+\\frac{15}{2}$$ ……(2);$$\\Rightarrow  2x+5 = -\\frac{1}{2}x+\\frac{15}{2}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  4x+10 = -x + 15$$;$$\\Rightarrow  5x=5$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x=1$$;with x =1,(1) gives y = 2(1) + 5 = 7;therefore coordinates of N = (1, 7) (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (116,'199700101003','L.H.S = $$\\frac{ (1+\\cos A)}{(1-\\cos A)}- \\frac{ (1-\\cos A)}{(1+\\cos A)}$$ ;= $$\\frac{ ((1+\\cos A)^2-(1-\\cos A)^2)}{((1-\\cos A)(1+\\cos A))}$$;= $$\\frac{ ((2\\cos A)(2))}{(1-\\cos ^2A)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (4\\cos A)}{(\\sin ^2A)}$$;= $$4\\frac{\\cos A}{\\sin A} \\frac{1}{\\sin A}$$;= $$4\\cot A\\csc A$$;=R.H.S (Proven)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (117,'199700101004','$$y=x^2+\\frac{24}{x}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=2x-\\frac{24}{x^2}$$;gradient of the curve at P = $$2(2)- \\frac{24}{(2)^2}$$;= 4-6;=-2;Equation of the line tangent to the curve at point  P(2, 16) is $$\\frac{ (y-16)}{(x-2)}=-2 \\Rightarrow  y-16 = -2x+4$$;i.e. y = -2x + 20.... equation of tangent to curve at P;x-c\\infty rdinate of A is given by 0 = -2x + 20;x = 10;i.e. A(10, 0);y-c\\infty rdinate of B is given by y = 20;i.e. B(0, 20);Area of triangle AOB;= $$\\frac{1}{2}(10)(20)$$;= $$100 sq units$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (118,'199700101005','Volume of the cylinder, V ;= (circular base area) x (height);= $$(\\pi r^2) \\times (4r)$$;= $$4\\pi r^3cm^3$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} r}=4\\pi (3r^2)$$;=$$12\\pi r^2cm^2$$;From $$\\frac{(gradV)}{(gradr)} = \\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} r}\\Rightarrow gradV = \\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} r}|_{(r=5)}(gradr)$$;where;$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} V}{\\mathrm{d} r}|_{r=5}=12\\pi (5)^2=300\\pi cm^2$$;$$gradr=(5+p)-5=pcm$$;therefore $$gradV = 300\\pi pcm^2$$;Percentage increase in V = $$\\frac{ (gradV)}{V}  \\times  100%$$;= $$\\frac{ (300\\pi p)}{(4\\pi (5)^3)} \\times 100%$$;= $$\\frac{ (3p)}{5}  \\times 100%$$;= $$60p%$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (119,'199700101006','a) Gradient of the curve at P = 5;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=4x-7=5$$;$$x=\\frac{ (5+7)}{4}=3$$;Use y = 2x y =2(3) = 6;Hence P(3, 6) (ANS);b) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 4x-7$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\int dy = \\int  4x-7dx$$;$$\\Rightarrow  y = 2x^2-7x+c$$;Using P(3, 6) we have,;$$6=2(3)^2-7(3)+c \\Rightarrow  c=6-18+21=9$$;therefore $$y=2x^2-7x+9$$');
