INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (123,'199700101011','a) i) $$gf(7)=g{f(7)}$$;=$$g{4(7)-17}$$;=$$g(11)$$;=$$ \\frac{5}{(2(11)-7)}$$;=$$ \\frac{5}{15}$$;=$$\\frac{1}{3}$$ ;$$f^2(x)=f{f(x)}$$;=$$f{4x-17}$$;=$$4(4x-7)-17$$;=$$16x-85$$;$$\\Rightarrow  16x-85 =\\frac{1}{3}$$;$$16x=\\frac{256}{3}$$;$$x=\\frac{16}{3} or 5 \\frac{1}{3}$$ (ANS);ii)f(x) = 4x - 17 ;Let;$$f(x)=4x-17 \\Rightarrow  x=\\frac{1}{4}(y+17)$$;$$i.e  f^{-1}(x)=\\frac{1}{4}(x+17)$$ …..(1);Similarly for $$g(x)= \\frac{5}{(2x-7)}$$;Let;$$y=\\frac{5}{(2x-7)}\\Rightarrow  x=\\frac{1}{2}(\\frac{5}{y}+7)$$;$$i.e  g^-1(x)=\\frac{1}{2}(\\frac{5}{x}+7),x\\neq 0$$ …..(2);Equating (1) and (2) yield,;$$\\frac{1}{4}(x+17)=\\frac{1}{2}(\\frac{5}{x}+7)$$;Multiple by;$$4x \\Rightarrow  x(x+17)=2(5+7x)$$;$$\\Rightarrow x^2+17x-14x-10=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow x^2+3x-10=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (x+5)(x-2)$$;i.e x = - 5 or x = 2 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (124,'199700101012','a) Height of the triangle;= $$\\sqrt{(5x)^2+(12x)^2}$$;=$$13xcm$$;therefore area of the triangular face of the pyramid;= $$\\frac{1}{2}(13x)(10x)$$;=$$65x^2cm^2$$ (ANS);b) Total surface area of the rectangular sides; = 4(10x)(h);= $$260xhcm^2$$;  Total surface area of the rectangular faces;= $$4  \\times  (65x^2)$$;=$$260x^2cm^2$$;therefore total area of metal sheet needed;= $$40xh+260x^2cm^2$$;$$\\Rightarrow  40xh +260x^2=1200$$;$$\\Rightarrow  2xh + 13x^2=60$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2xh=60-13x^2$$;i.e. $$h=\\frac{ (60-13x^2)}{(2x)}$$ (SHOWN);c) Volume of the inverted regular pyramid;= $$\\frac{1}{3}  \\times  (100x^2)  \\times  12x = 400x^3cm^3$$;  Volume of the rectangular top with rectangular sides;= $$100x^2hcm^3$$;$$\\Rightarrow  volume of container=100x^2h+400x^3cm^3$$;  i.e. volume V = $$100x^2(\\frac{ (60-13x^2)}{(2x)})+400x^3$$;=$$3000x-650x^3+400x^3$$;=$$3000x-250x^3cm^3$$ (SHOWN);iv) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 3000-750x^2$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} ^{2}y}{\\mathrm{d} x^{2}}=-1500x$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 0 \\Rightarrow  x^2 =\\frac{ 3000}{750} = 4$$;i.e x = 2 cm (ANS);at x = 2 cm,;Volume V =$$3000x-250x^3cm^3$$;=3000(2) - 250(2)^3;=$$ 4000 cm^3$$ (ANS);$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} ^{2}y}{\\mathrm{d} x^{2}}=-3000 = -ve$$;Hence the volume V has a maximum value at x = 2 cm. (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (125,'199700101013','a) $$5\\cos ^2x-8\\sin x\\cos x=0$$; $$\\Rightarrow  \\cos x(5\\cos x-8\\sin x)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\cos x=0 or 5\\cos x-8\\sin x=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x=90^{\\circ},270^{\\circ}or \\tan x=\\frac{5}{8}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x=90^{\\circ},270^{\\circ} or x=32^{\\circ},212^{\\circ}$$;therefore $$x=32^{\\circ}, 90^{\\circ}, 212^{\\circ} or 270^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);b) $$5\\tan ^2y+7=11secy$$;$$\\Rightarrow  5(sec^2y-1)+7=11secy$$;$$\\Rightarrow  5sec^2y-11secy+2=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (5secy-1)(secy-2)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  secy=\\frac{1}{5} or sec y =2$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\cos y=5 (rejected) or \\cos y=\\frac{1}{2} $$;i.e $$y=60^{\\circ} or 300^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);c) $$1+2\\sin (\\frac{ (3z)}{2 }+75^{\\circ})=0^{\\circ}$$	;Let  x = $$\\frac{ (3z)}{2 }+75^{\\circ}\\Rightarrow  1+2\\sin x=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\sin x=-\\frac{1}{2}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x = 210^{\\circ},330^{\\circ},570^{\\circ}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\frac{ (3z)}{2}+75^{\\circ} = 210^{\\circ},330^{\\circ},570^{\\circ}$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{ (3z)}{2} = 135^{\\circ},255^{\\circ},495^{\\circ}$$;	i.e $$z=90^{\\circ},170^{\\circ},330^{\\circ}$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (126,'199700101014','a) $$AB = \\sqrt{(9-3)^2 + (6+2)^2}=\\sqrt{36+64}=10$$;$$BC=\\sqrt{(-8)^2+(h+2)^2}=\\sqrt{h^2+4h+68}$$;$$AB=BC$$;$$\\Rightarrow  h^2+4h+68=100$$;$$\\Rightarrow  h^2+4h-32=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (h-4)(h+8)=0$$;	  h = 4 or h = - 8(rejected) (ANS); b) Gradient of line AB = $$\\frac{ (9-3)}{(6-(-2))}= \\frac{6}{8}=\\frac{3}{4}$$ Gradient of line BC = $$\\frac{ (-5-3)}{(h+2)}=- \\frac{8}{6}=-\\frac{4}{3}$$;Now	$$(\\frac{3}{4})(-\\frac{4}{3})=-1$$;Therefore angle ABC is a right angle. (SHOWN);c)M is the mid-point  of line joining A(6, 9) and B(-2, 3), hence;M = $$((\\frac{1}{2}(6-2)),(\\frac{1}{2}(9+3)))=(2,6)$$ ;P = $$((\\frac{1}{2}(6+h)),(\\frac{1}{2}(9-5)))=(5,2)$$;Line MP : y = mx + c where ;M = gradient of MP = $$\\frac{ (6-2)}{(2-5)}= \\frac{4}{-3}$$;Use M = $$(2,6)$$;$$\\Rightarrow  6=2(\\frac{-4}{3})+c$$;$$\\Rightarrow  c= 6+\\frac{8}{3}=\\frac{26}{3}$$ ;Therefore, ;$$y=-\\frac{4}{3x}+\\frac{26}{3}$$ …equation of line MPQ;To find Q, substitute y = 0 into above equation, we have,;$$0=-\\frac{4}{3x}+\\frac{26}{3} or x=\\frac{26}{4}=1\\frac{3}{2}$$;hence, Q = $$(1\\frac{3}{2},0)$$;Therefore, $$M= (2,6)$$, $$P=(5,2)$$, $$Q=(1\\frac{3}{2},0)$$ (ANS);d)$$MP = \\sqrt{(6-2)^2+(2-5)^2}=\\sqrt{25}=5$$;$$BC = \\sqrt{(5-1\\frac{3}{2})^2+(2-0)^2}=\\sqrt{(\\frac{3}{2})^2+2^2}=\\sqrt{\\frac{25}{4}}=\\frac{5}{2}$$;therefore; MP:PQ= $$5: \\frac{5}{2}$$;= 2:1 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (127,'199700101015','a) $$\\tan (APQ)=\\frac{3}{5}=0.6$$;$$\\Rightarrow  angle APQ = \\tan ^{-1}(0.6)$$;= $$30.96^{\\circ}$$ ;= $$0.172\\pi  radians$$;i.e   $$\\angle APB = 2(0.172p)$$;$$ =0.344p$$;	       $$=1.08 radians$$ (SHOWN);b)   Sector AXB has an angle ;= $$(2\\pi -1.08)=5.20 radians$$;$$\\Rightarrow  arc length AXB = (5.20)(5)+26.0cm $$; Similarly,angle AQB= $$\\pi -1.08=2.06 radians$$;Sector AYB has an angle = (2p - 2.06) = 4.22 radians;or length AYB = 4.22(3) = 12.66 cm;therefore perimeter of XAYBX;= 26.0+12.66 = 38.66 cm (ANS);c) Area of sector AXB =$$\\frac{1}{2}$$ (5) (26.0) = $$65cm^2$$ ;Area of sector AYB =$$\\frac{1}{2}$$ (3) (12.66) = 18.99 $$\\approx 19cm^2$$ ;Area of quadrilateral APBQ ;= 2(area of triangle APQ);= $$2(\\frac{1}{2}(5)(3))$$;= $$15cm^2$$;therefore area of shape XAYBX = 65 + 19 +15 =$$99 cm^2$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (128,'199700101016','a) Area = $$\\int _{x=2}^3y_1-y_2dx$$;= $$\\int _2^3[(6x-x^2-5)-(x^2-4x+7)]dx$$;= $$\\int _2^3(10x-2x^2-12)dx$$;= $$[5x^2-\\frac{2}{3}x^3-12x]_2^3$$;= $$(45-18-36-(20-\\frac{16}{3}-24))$$;= $$\\frac{1}{3} units^2$$ (ANS);b) v = $$\\pi \\int _1^3[(x+4)^2-(2x+\\frac{3}{x})^2]dx$$;$$\\Rightarrow  v=\\pi \\int _1^3[x^2+8x+16-(4x^2+12x+\\frac{9}{(x^2)})]dx$$;$$\\Rightarrow  v=\\pi \\int _1^3[-3x^2+8x+4-\\frac{9}{(x^2)}]dx$$;$$\\Rightarrow  v = \\pi (-x^3+4x^2+4x-\\frac{9}{x})_1^3dx$$;= $$\\pi ((-27+36+12+3)-(-1+4+4+9))$$	;= $$8\\pi  units^3$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (129,'199700101017','a) Now $$\\vec{OA}=10i+9j$$ and $$\\vec{OB}=-14i+2j$$;$$\\vec{OA} \\ast \\vec{OB}=|\\vec{OA}||\\vec{OB}|\\cos  \\theta $$;$$\\Rightarrow  (10,9) \\ast (-14,2)=\\sqrt{10^2+9^2}\\sqrt{14^2+2^2}\\cos \\theta $$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\sqrt{181}\\sqrt{200}\\cos \\theta =-140+18=-122$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\cos  \\theta  = - \\frac{122}{\\sqrt{181}\\sqrt{200}}=0.6412$$;i.e.$$\\theta =\\pi -\\cos ^{-1}(0.6412)$$;=$$\\pi -50.12^{\\circ}$$;=$$129.88$$;$$\\approx 130^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);b)  $$\\vec{AP}=\\vec{OP}-\\vec{OA}$$;=$$(p,13)-(10,9)$$;=$$(p-10,4)$$;=$$(p-10)i+4j$$ (ANS);$$\\vec{BP}=\\vec{OP}-\\vec{OB}$$;=$$(p,13)-(-14,2)$$;=$$(p+14,11)$$;=$$(p+14)i+11j$$ (ANS)c) Now$$\\vec{AP} \\ast \\vec{BP}=0 \\Rightarrow  (P-10)(P+14)+4(11)=0$$$$\\Rightarrow  P^2+4P-140+44=0$$$$\\Rightarrow  P^2+4P-96=0$$$$\\Rightarrow  (P-8)(P+12)=0$$i.e$$P=8 or P=-12$$ (ANS)iv) $$AP = BP$$$$\\Rightarrow |\\vec{AP}|^2=|\\vec{BP}|^2$$$$\\Rightarrow  (P-10)^2+4^2=(P+14)^2+11^2$$$$\\Rightarrow  P^2-20P+116=P^2+28P+196+121$$$$\\Rightarrow  48P=116-196-121=-201$$;$$\\Rightarrow  P=-20\\frac{1}{4}8$$;$$= - 4.1875$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (130,'199700102001','a) $$f(x)=ax^3-4x^2+bx-5$$;$$\\Rightarrow f(-1)=0 or b+a=9$$ …..(1);$$f(3)=4$$;$$9a+b=15$$……(2);(2) - (1) yield  8a =24 or a =3 ;use a = 3 in (1), we have b = - 9 - a = - 12;Therefore $$f(x)=3x^3-4x^2-12x-5$$;The remainder when f(x) is divided by x - 2 is ;f(2) = 24 - 16 - 24 - 5 = - 21 (ANS) ;b)$$x^2=5+\\frac{2}{x}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x^3=5x+2$$;$$\\Rightarrow x^3-5x-2=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow (x+2)(x^2-2x-1)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=-2 or x^2-2x-1=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=-2; or x=\\frac{ (2+- \\sqrt{4+4})}{2}$$; = $$1+-\\sqrt2$$; = $$1+-1.4142$$; = 2.41 or 0.41;therefore solutions to the equation are x = - 2, - 0.41 or 2.41 correct to 2 decimal places. (ANS);c) Let f(x) = $$x^2-6x-9$$;By Remainder Theorem	;$$\\Rightarrow  f(p)=p^2-6p-9=$$ remainder when f(x) is divided by x-p;$$\\Rightarrow  f(-q)=q^2+6q-9=$$ remainder when f(x) is divided by x+q;Now f(p) = f( - q) and $$p \\neq q$$;$$\\Rightarrow  p^2-6p-9=q^2+6q-9$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (p^2-q^2)-6(p+q)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (p-q)(p+q)-6(p+q)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (p+q)(p-q-6)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  p-q-6=0  since  p\\neq -q or p+q \\neq 0$$;i.e p - q = 6 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (131,'199700102002','a) Let a =50 = first term of the G.P and r = common ratio of the G.P;i) $$T_4=10.8 \\Rightarrow  ar^3=10.8\\Rightarrow r^3=\\frac{10.8}{50}=0.216 $$;i.e. r = $$(0.216)^{\\frac{1}{3}}=0.6$$;Therefore ;$$T_5=ar^4=50(0.6)^4$$;= 6.48 (ANS);ii) Sum to infinity, ;$$S_\\infty = \\frac{a}{(1-r)}; |r|<1$$;$$\\Rightarrow  S_\\infty =\\frac{ 50}{(1-(0.6))}= \\frac{50}{0.4}$$;= 125 (ANS);iii)$$T_n<0.25$$;$$\\Rightarrow  ar^{n-1}<0.25$$;$$\\Rightarrow  50(0.6)^{n-1}<0.25$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (0.6)^{n-1}<0.005$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (n-1)\\log (0.6)>(\\log 0.005)$$;$$\\Rightarrow  n-1>\\frac{ (\\log (0.005))}{(\\log 0.6)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  n>1+\\frac{ (\\log (0.005))}{(\\log 0.6)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  n>1+\\frac{ (-2.3010)}{(-0.2218)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  n>11.37$$;i.e n = 12 the smallest integer such that $$T_n<0.25$$ (ANS);	b) i) Given sales of television in 1996 is 38400;$$\\Rightarrow  S_12=38400$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\frac{12}{2}[2a+11(200)]=38400$$;$$\\Rightarrow  2a+2200 = \\frac{38400}{6}=6400$$;$$\\Rightarrow  2a=4200$$;i.e. a = 2100 or 2100 sets of television are sold in January of 1996. (ANS);ii) Sales of television in December of 1996;= $$T_12$$;= a + 11d;= 2100 + 11(200);= 4300 (ANS);c) $$T_1$$ = first term of the sequence = 210 = 15 x 14	;$$T_N$$ =last term of the sequence = 990 = 15 x 66;To find the sum from $$T_1$$ to $$T_N$$, need to determine the number of terms in the sequence which is given by:;$$n=\\frac{ (T_n-T_1)}{15} + 1$$;$$\\Rightarrow  n=(66-14)+1$$;i.e n = 53;therefore sum of the numbers ;= $$\\frac{n}{2}(T_1+T_n)=5\\frac{3}{2}(210+990)$$;= 31800 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (132,'199700102003','a) Now ;$$3\\cos x-2\\sin x+1=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\sqrt{13}\\cos (x+33.7^{\\circ})=-1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\cos (x+33.7^{\\circ})=-0.27735$$;$$\\Rightarrow x+33.7^{\\circ}=106.10^{\\circ},253.90^{\\circ}$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=72.4^{\\circ} or 220.2^{\\circ}$$ ;b) $$y = 5(1-\\cos  2x)$$ ; $$0\\leq x\\leq \\frac{\\pi }{2}$$ radians;i) when x = 1;$$\\Rightarrow  y=5(1-\\cos 2x)$$;=5[1-(-0.416)];= 7.08 (ANS);ii) when y = 3;$$\\Rightarrow  3=5(1-\\cos 2x)$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\cos 2x=1-\\frac{3}{5}=0.4$$;$$\\Rightarrow  2x=1.1593$$;$$x = 0.5796 \\approx 0.58 rads$$ (ANS);iii) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = 5(\\sin 2x)(2)=10\\sin 2x$$;at x = $$\\frac{\\pi }{4}$$,;gradient of the curve is ;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}|_{x=\\frac{\\pi }{4}}=10\\sin (\\frac{\\pi }{2})=10(1)$$;	= 10 (ANS);c) Given \\tan  A = 2 \\tan  B;Now;$$\\tan (A-B)= \\frac{ (\\tan A-\\tan B)}{(1+\\tan A\\tan B)}$$;=$$ \\frac{\\tan B}{(1+2\\tan ^2B)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow (\\tan A-B)= \\frac{ (\\frac{\\sin B}{\\cos B})}{(1+2\\frac{ (\\sin ^2B)}{(\\cos ^2B)})}$$;= $$\\frac{ (\\sin B\\cos B)}{(\\cos ^2B+2\\sin ^2B)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\tan (A-B)= \\frac{ (\\frac{1}{2}\\sin 2B)}{(( \\frac{ (1+\\cos 2B)}{2})}+2(\\frac{ (1-\\cos 2B)}{2}))$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\tan (A-B)= \\frac{ (\\sin 2B)}{((1+\\cos 2B)+2(1-\\cos 2B))}$$;i.e $$\\tan (A-B)= \\frac{ (\\sin 2B)}{(3-\\cos 2B)}$$ (SHOWN)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (133,'199700102004','a) i) From ;$$y=Ab^x$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\log  y = \\log (Ab^x)$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\log A+\\log (b^x)$$;$$= \\log  A + x \\log  b$$(ANS);ii) Rewrite the table in the form of log  y versus x to plot a straight line;img;img; From the graph,;Gradient = $$\\frac{0.775}{3.50}=0.2214$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\log  b = gradient = -0.2214$$;i.e $$b=10^{-0.2214}$$; =0.60 (ANS);y-intercept = 0.895;$$\\Rightarrow  \\log A=\\log y|_{x=0} = 0.895$$;i.e $$a=10^{0.895} \\approx  7.85$$ (ANS);iii)At x = 0.8,;$$y=7.85(0.60)^{0.8}=5.2166$$;$$\\approx  5.22$$ (ANS);b)i) $$\\frac{y}{\\sqrt{x} }versus  x^2$$ is a straight line with point s (3, 5) and (5, 1) on the line. ;Using the gradient from these two point s, we may write;$$ \\frac{ ( \\frac{y}{\\sqrt{x}}-1)}{(x^2-5)}= \\frac{ (1-5)}{(5-3)}=-2$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{y}{\\sqrt x}=-2x^2+11$$;i.e $$y=(-2x^2+11)\\sqrt x=11x^{(\\frac{1}{2})}-2x^{\\frac{1}{2}}$$ (ANS);ii) when x = 4,;$$\\Rightarrow  y=11(4)^{\\frac{1}{2}}-2(4)^{(\\frac{1}{2})}$$;= 22 - 64;= - 42 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (134,'199700102005','a) i) $$x=\\theta |_{t=0}=18+62=80^{\\circ}C$$ (ANS); ii) when t = 16,;$$\\theta =18+62e^{-2}$$;= 18 + 62(0.1353);= $$26.39^{\\circ}C$$ (ANS);iii) when \\thetah = 48,;$$\\Rightarrow  48=18+62e^{-\\frac{t}{8}}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  t=-8\\ln (\\frac{30}{62})$$;= 5.81 (ANS);iv)$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} \\theta }{\\mathrm{d} t} =-\\frac{62}{8}e^{\\frac{-t}{8}}=-3\\frac{1}{4}e^{\\frac{-t}{8}}$$;At t =16, rate at which \\theta is decreasing = ;$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} \\theta }{\\mathrm{d} t|_{t=16}}=-3\\frac{1}{4}e^{-\\frac{16}{8}}=1.0488$$;= - 1.05 (ANS);As $$t \\rightarrow \\infty ,e^{-\\frac{t}{8}} \\rightarrow 0$$;and hence $$\\theta  \\approx  18$$ as t becomes very large (ANS);b i)$$\\lg x+\\lg [5(x+1)]=2$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\lg [5x(x+1)]=2$$;$$\\Rightarrow 5x(x+1)=10^2=100$$;$$\\Rightarrow x^2+x=20$$;$$\\Rightarrow  x^2+x-20=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow (x-4)(x+5)=0$$;i.e $$x=-5 or x=4$$; therefore x = 4 (ANS)ii) $$3^{(y+1)}=0.45$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\lg (3^{y+1})=\\lg (0.45)$$;$$\\Rightarrow (y+1)\\lg 3=\\lg 0.45$$;$$\\Rightarrow y=\\frac{ (\\lg 0.45)}{(\\lg 3)}-1=\\frac{ (\\lg 0.45-\\lg 3)}{(\\lg 3)}= \\frac{ (\\lg 0.15)}{(\\lg 3)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow y=-1.7268$$;i.e y = - 1.73 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (135,'199700102006','a) $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x}(\\frac{ (2x+3)}{(x-4)})= \\frac{ ((x-4)(2)-(2x+3)(1))}{((x-4)^2)}$$;= $$\\frac{ ((2x-8)-(2x+3))}{((x-4)^2)}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (-11)}{((x-4)^2)}$$;i.e k = - 11 (ANS);b)$$y^2x^3=72$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x}(y^2x^3)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  (2y\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x})x^3+(3x^2)(y^2)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  2y\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=-3x^2y^2$$;i.e $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{ (-3y)}{(2x)}$$ (SHOWN);At $$y=3\\Rightarrow 9x^2=72\\Rightarrow x^3=8\\Rightarrow x=2$$;The point  on the curve is thus (2, 3).;Gradient to the curve at point  (2, 3) is thus;gradient = $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}|_{y=3}=\\frac{ (-3(3))}{(2(2))}= \\frac{ (-9)}{4}$$;	    therefore normal to the curve at ;(y = 3) = $$\\frac{-1}{gradient}$$;           = $$\\frac{4}{9}$$ (ANS);   c) Given ;$$y=(x-4)\\sqrt{6+x}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\sqrt{6+x}+\\frac{ (x-4)}{(2\\sqrt{6+x})}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = \\frac{ (2(6+x)+x-4)}{(2\\sqrt{6+x})}=\\frac{ (3x+8)}{(2\\sqrt{6+x})}$$;at stationary point , ;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow  3x+8=0$$;i.e $$x=-\\frac{8}{3}$$;  The x-coordinate of the stationary point  on the curve is $$x=-\\frac{8}{3}$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (136,'199700102007','a) $$\\int (3\\sin x-4\\cos 2x)dx=3\\int \\sin xdx-4\\int \\cos 2xdx$$;= $$3(-\\cos x)-4(\\frac{1}{2}\\sin 2x)+C$$  ;i.e $$\\int (3\\sin x-4\\cos 2x)dx=-3\\cos x-2\\sin 2x+C$$ where C is an integration constant. (ANS);b) From;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x} = \\sqrt{1+2x}$$;$$\\Rightarrow  y=\\int dy=\\int (1+2x)dx$$;i.e $$y=\\frac{1}{3}(1+2x)^{\\frac{3}{2}}+C$$ ….. equation of the curve ;To determine C, the integration constant, substitute (4, 30) into the equation. Hence,;$$30=\\frac{1}{3}(1+2(4))^{\\frac{3}{2}}+C$$;$$\\Rightarrow  30=\\frac{1}{3}(9)^{\\frac{3}{2}}+C$$;$$\\Rightarrow  30=9+C$$;$$C=21$$;therefore $$y=\\frac{1}{3}(1+2x)^{\\frac{3}{2}}+21$$ is the equation of the curve. (ANS);c) Given $$y=2+\\frac{1}{(x+1)}$$;i) Area of the shaded region;= $$\\int _{x=0}^2ydx$$;=$$\\int _0^2(2+\\frac{1}{(x+1)})dx$$;=$$[2x+\\ln (x+1)]_0^2$$;= 4 + \\ln  3;= $$5.0986  units^2$$ (ANS);ii) Volume of the generated object;= $$\\pi \\int _0^2y^2dx$$;= $$\\pi \\int _0^2(2+\\frac{1}{(x+1)})^2dx$$;= $$\\pi \\int _0^2(4+\\frac{4}{(x+1)}+ \\frac{1}{(x+1)^2)}dx$$;= $$\\pi [4x+4\\ln (x+1)- \\frac{1}{(x+1)}]_0^2$$;$$\\Rightarrow  Volume = \\pi [(8+4\\ln 3-\\frac{1}{3})-(-1)]$$;=$$\\pi (8\\frac{2}{3}+4\\ln 3)$$;$$\\approx  41.03 units^3$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (137,'199700102008','i) Given;$$x=t^2+3t,y=t^2-2t$$;$$\\Rightarrow  4(t^2-2t)+(t^2+3t)=10$$;$$\\Rightarrow  5t^2-5t=10$$;$$\\Rightarrow t^2-t-2=10$$;$$(t-1)(t+1)=0$$;i.e t = -1 or t = 2 (ANS);ii)   $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x }{\\mathrm{d} t}=2t+3, \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=2t-2$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}}{\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}}$$;=$$\\frac{ (2t-2)}{(2t+3)}$$ (ANS);iii)$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{(2t-2)}{(2t+3)}=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow t=1$$;when t =1, x = 4  y = -1;therefore the coordinates of the stationary point  of the curve is (4, -1). (ANS);iv)Normal = $$-\\frac{1}{gradient}=-\\frac{1}{\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}}=-\\frac{ (2t+3)}{(2t-2)}$$	if  Normal is parallel t o the x-axis ,then,;2t + 3 =0;$$\\Rightarrow  t=-\\frac{3}{2}$$;when $$\\Rightarrow  t=-\\frac{3}{2}$$;$$x=-\\frac{9}{4}$$;$$y=2\\frac{1}{4}$$;therefore the coordinates of the point s on the curve at which  the tangent is parallel to the y-axis $$(\\frac{-9}{4},2\\frac{1}{4})$$;  To draw the curve for $$-3\\leq t\\leq 2$$, we tabulate the values of x and y in the following table ;img;$$x=t^2+3t$$;$$y=t^2-2t$$;Plot the graph of y versus x according to the tabulated values.;img;Curve of $$x=t^2+3t,y=t^2-2t$$;From ;$$x=t^2+3t$$ ……(1);$$y=t^2-2t$$ …….(2); (1)-(2);$$\\Rightarrow  5t=x-y$$;$$t=\\frac{(x-y)}{5}$$ ……(3);Similarly 2 x (1) + 3 x (2);$$\\Rightarrow 5t^2=2x+3y$$;$$t^2=(\\frac{ (2x+3y)}{5})$$ ……(4);From equations (3) and (4), we have,;$$( \\frac{ (x-y)}{5})^2=(\\frac{ (2x+3y)}{5})$$;$$\\Rightarrow 5(2x+3y)=(x-y)^2$$;i.e $$x^2+y^2-2xy-10x-15y=0$$ is the cartesian equation of the curve. (ANS)');
