INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (139,'199700103002','a) From $$y=\\frac{1}{2}x-1 \\Rightarrow  m=\\frac{1}{2}$$	Using A =(4, 6);we thus have $$6=\\frac{1}{2}(4)+c\\Rightarrow c=6-2=4$$;therefore $$y=\\frac{1}{2}x+4$$ …… line of equation of AB;To find B, substitute ; $$x=0\\Rightarrow y=4$$;therefore coordinates of B is (0, 4) (ANS);b) Now gradient of line AC = $$-\\frac{1}{(\\frac{1}{2})}=-2$$;therefore line equation of AC is of the form y = - 2x + D;Substitute A =(4, 6) into the equation, we have,;$$6=-2(4)+D\\Rightarrow D=14$$;therefore $$ y = - 2x + 14$$.....line of equation of AC.;To find C, solve the simultaneous equations,;$$6=-2(4)+D \\Rightarrow  D=14$$;Subst (1):into (2), we have,;$$2(-2x+14)=x-2$$;$$\\Rightarrow 5x=2(14)+2=30$$;therefore x = 6 and y = - 2x + 14 =- 2(6) +14 = 2;Hence coordinates of C is (6, 2). (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (140,'199700103003','Given $$y=4x^2-6x+11$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=8x-6$$;=$$2(4x-3)$$;since the line y = 2x + c is tangent to the curve,;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=2(4x-3)=2\\Rightarrow x=1$$;At x = 1, y = 9;therefore the line y = 2x + c is tangent to the curve at point  (1, 9).;To find c, substitute (1, 9) into the equation,;$$\\Rightarrow 9=2(1)+c$$;c = 9-2 = 7;When x = 0, y = 7; y = 0, x = $$-\\frac{7}{2}$$therefore $$A(-\\frac{7}{2}) and B(0,7)$$;Area of triangle OAB = $$\\frac{1}{2}(\\vec{OA})(\\vec{OB})$$;  =$$\\frac{1}{2}(\\frac{7}{2})(7)$$; = $$\\frac{49}{4}units^2$$ (ANS)');
