INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (181,'199800102001','a) Let $$f(x)=4x^4-9a^2x^2+2(a^2-7)x-18$$;since f(x) is divisible by (2x - 3a), by factor theorem,;$$f(\\frac{3}{2}a)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow 4(\\frac{3}{2}a)^4-9a^2(\\frac{3}{2}a)^2+2(a^2-7)(\\frac{3}{2}a)-18=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow\\frac{ (81a^4)}{4}-\\frac{ (81a^4)}{4+3a(a^2-7)}-18=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow a^3-7a-6=0$$ (shown);To find a, we solve for a from the equation;$$a^3-7a-6=0$$;Now when a = - 1,;$$a^3-7a-6=-1+7-6=0$$;Therefore (a + 1) is a factor of ;$$a^3-7a-6$$;$$\\Rightarrow a^3-7a-6=(a+1)(a^2-a-6)$$;$$=(a+1)(a+2)(a-3)$$;therefore;$$a^3-7a-6=(a+1)(a+2)(a-3)=0$$;Hence a = -1, or a = 2 or a = 3 (ANS);b) Let;$$f(x)=2x^3+bx^2-cx+d$$;since f(x) has the same remainder when divided by x +1 or x - 2 or 2x - 1, then;$$f(-1)=f(2)=f(\\frac{1}{2})$$;$$\\Rightarrow -2+b+c+d=16+4b-2c+d$$;=$$\\frac{1}{4}+\\frac{1}{4}b-\\frac{1}{2}c+d$$;$$\\Rightarrow -2+b+c+d=16+4b-2c+d$$;$$\\Rightarrow -2+b+c+d=\\frac{1}{4}+\\frac{1}{4}b-\\frac{1}{2}c+d$$;$$\\Rightarrow b-c=-6$$ …….(1);$$\\Rightarrow b+2c=3$$ ……(2);Solving the two equations, we have ;(2) - (1) ;3c = 3 + 6 = 9;c = 3 (ANS);and hence b = 3 - 2c = - 3 (ANS);Now;$$f(x)=2x^3-3x^2-3x+d$$;since f(x) is exactly divisible by ( x + 2), we have ;f(- 2) = 0;- 16 - 12 + 6 + d = 0;therefore d = 22 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (182,'199800102002','a) The length of sides of polygon are in A.P.;Thus a = first term of the A.P = length of the shortest side of polygon = 1.3 m.;b = last term of the A.P = length of the longest side of polygon = 5.7 m.;$$\\Rightarrow 42=\\frac{1}{2}n(1.3+5.7)\\Rightarrow n=\\frac{84}{7.0}=12$$;Thus the polygon has 12 sides. (ANS);b) $$T_1$$ = first term of G.P = 25 = a;$$S_1$$ = sum of the first three terms of G.P;= $$a\\frac{ (1-r^3)}{(1-r)}$$;= $$25(\\frac{ (1-r^3)}{(1-r)})$$  ;where r = common ratio of G.P.;$$\\Rightarrow 25(\\frac{ (1-r^3)}{(1-r)})=61\\Rightarrow 25(r^2+r+1)=61$$;$$\\Rightarrow 25r^2+25r-36=0\\Rightarrow (5r+9)(5r-4)=0$$;$$r=-\\frac{9}{5 }or r=\\frac{4}{5}$$;since the G.P has a sum to infinity, then |r| < 1and hence ;$$r=\\frac{4}{5}$$(ANS);Therefore;$$S_oo=\\frac{a}{(1-r)}=\\frac{25}{(1-\\frac{4}{5})}=(25)(5)=125$$ (ANS);c)i) The distances walked by the man form a G.P.;Thus a = distance walked on first day dated 1st June = 35 km;r = common ratio of G.P = 95% = 0.95;Now on 10th June, he has already continued his journey for 10 days, thus distance walked is;$$d=S_10=a(\\frac{ (1-r^10)}{(1-r)c})$$;=$$35(\\frac{ (1-0.95^10)}{(1-0.95)})=700(1-0.5987)$$;=$$280.91$$;$$\\approx 281km$$ (ANS);ii) To complete the walk, if n is the number of days he walks, then;$$S_n\\geq 480$$;$$\\Rightarrow 35(\\frac{ (1-0.95^n)}{(1-0.95)})\\geq 480$$;$$\\Rightarrow 1-0.95^n\\geq 0.6857$$;$$\\Rightarrow 0.95^n\\leq 0.3143$$;$$\\Rightarrow n\\geq \\frac{(\\log (0.3143))}{(\\log 0.95)}since \\log  0.95<0)$$;$$\\Rightarrow n\\geq \\frac{ (-0.5027)}{(-0.02228)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow n\\geq 22.56$$;Thus n is 23. i.e he needs 23 days to complete the journey. Hence he will complete the walk on 23rd June. (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (183,'199800102003','img;(See graph of $$y \\sqrt x$$ versus $$x \\sqrt x$$ );img;i) Thus, from the graph,;a = gradient of line;$$\\approx \\frac{-9.3}{7.65}$$;$$\\approx -1.2157$$;$$\\approx -1.2$$ (ANS)  ;b = intercept of line with vertical axis = 9.3 (ANS);ii) When ;$$xy=4\\sqrt x \\Rightarrow y\\sqrt x=4$$;From the graph,;$$x\\sqrt x=4.4$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=(4.4)^{\\frac{2}{3}}=2.685$$;$$\\approx 2.7$$ (ANS);b) From the given sketch;$$ \\frac{ ( \\frac{y}{x-1})}{(x-1)}= \\frac{ (-3-1)}{(5-1)}= \\frac{ (-4)}{4}=1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{y}{x}-1=1-x$$;$$\\frac{y}{x}=2-x$$;$$y=x(2-x)$$ (ANS);y is a quadratic function of x. It has a maximum at x =1 with y = 1and t he curve cuts the x-axis at x =0 and x = 2.;img;img;img');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (184,'199800102004','a) i) $$3\\cos x-2\\sin x=1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\sqrt{3^2+2^2}\\cos (x+\\tan ^{-1}(\\frac{2}{3}))=1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\cos (x+33.69^{\\circ} )=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{13}}$$;$$\\Rightarrow x+33.69^{\\circ} =\\cos ^{-1}(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{13}})=73.90^{\\circ}  or 286.10^{\\circ} $$;$$\\Rightarrow x=40.21^{\\circ}  or x=252.41^{\\circ} $$ (ANS);ii)$$5\\sin y=secy$$;$$\\Rightarrow 5\\sin y=\\frac{1}{\\cos y}$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{5}{2}(2\\sin y\\cos y)=1$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\sin 2y=\\frac{2}{5}=0.4$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2y=23.58^{\\circ}  or 156.42^{\\circ}  or 383.58^{\\circ}  or 516.42^{\\circ} $$;$$\\Rightarrow y=11.79^{\\circ}  or 78.21^{\\circ}  or 191.79^{\\circ}  or 258.21^{\\circ} $$ (ANS);  b)$$\\tan (\\theta +45^{\\circ} )= \\frac{ (\\tan \\theta +\\tan 45^{\\circ} )}{(1-\\tan \\theta \\tan 45^{\\circ} )}= \\frac{ (1+\\tan \\theta )}{(1-\\tan \\theta )}$$; From the diagram,;$$\\tan (\\theta +45^{\\circ} )=\\frac{6}{h}$$;$$\\tan \\theta =\\frac{1}{h}$$;therefore;$$ \\frac{6}{h}=\\frac{1+\\frac{1}{h}}{1-\\frac{1}{h}}$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{6}{h}=\\frac{ (h+1)}{(h-1)}$$;$$\\Rightarrow h(h+1)=6(h-1)$$;$$\\Rightarrow h^2-5h+6=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow h=2 or h=3$$;Possible values of ');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (185,'199800102005','a) $$\\log _3(x-1)=2$$;$$\\Rightarrow x-1=3^2$$;$$\\Rightarrow x-1=9$$;$$x=10$$;$$\\lg x=1$$ (ANS);b)$$\\lg (3x+2)+6\\lg 2=2+\\lg (2x+1)$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\lg (3x+2)+\\lg 2^6=\\lg 10^2+\\lg (2x+1)$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\lg [2^6(3x+2)]=\\lg [10^2(2x+1)]$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2^6(3x+2)=10^2(2x+1)$$;$$\\Rightarrow 16(3x+2)=25(2x+1)$$;$$\\Rightarrow 48x+32=50x+25$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2x=7$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=\\frac{7}{2} =3.5$$ (ANS);c) $$e^{2x}-e^x-6=0$$;Let  $$y =e^x$$;then ;$$y^2=e^2x$$;$$\\Rightarrow y^2-y-6=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow (y-3)(y+2)=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow y=e^x=3 or -2(N.A)$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=\\ln 3=1.0986$$ (ANS);	     d) 	y = \\ln  (x + 2) for $$-1\\leq x\\leq 3$$;Now $$\\sqrt{x+2}=e^{1-x}$$;By taking natural \\log arithmic on both sides,;$$\\ln (\\sqrt{x+2})=1-x$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{2}\\ln (x+2)=1-x$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\ln (x+2)=2(1-x)$$;Thus, from the graph, solution of the equation is x = 0.55 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (186,'199800102006','a) i)$$ \\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x} \\cos ^2x$$;=$$(2\\cos x) \\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x} (\\cos x)$$;=$$(2\\cos x)(-\\sin x)$$;=$$-\\sin 2x$$ (ANS);ii)   $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x} (e^{(3-2x)})$$;=$$e^{(3-2x)}\\frac{\\mathrm{d} }{\\mathrm{d} x}(3-2x)$$;=$$-2e^{3-2x}$$ (ANS);b)$$y=\\frac{ (3x)}{(2x-3)}$$;=$$\\frac{3}{2}(\\frac{ (2x)}{(2x-3)})$$;=$$\\frac{3}{2}+\\frac{9}{(2(2x-3))}$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{9}{2}[-\\frac{2}{(2x-3)^2}]$$ ;=$$- \\frac{9}{(2x-3)^2}$$;$$\\Rightarrow -\\frac{9}{(2x-3)^2}=-\\frac{9}{4}$$;$$\\Rightarrow (2x-3)^2=4$$;$$\\Rightarrow 2x-3= \\pm 2$$;$$\\Rightarrow x=\\frac{5}{2} or x=\\frac{1}{2}$$ (ANS);c) $$xy^2-y^3+4=0$$;$$y=2\\Rightarrow 4x-8+4=0\\Rightarrow x=1$$;Thus the point on the curve is $$P -= (1, 2)$$.;Now by differentiating the given curve equation,;$$2xy\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}+y^2-3y^2\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=0$$;$$\\Rightarrow (3y-2x)\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=y$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{y}{(3y-2x)}$$;Thus at point $$P -= (1, 2)$$, gradient of curve is ;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{2}{(6-2)}= \\frac{2}{4}=\\frac{1}{2}$$ (ANS)');
