INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (262,'199900104003','a) $$\\lg (x-8)+\\lg (\\frac{9}{2})=1+\\lg (\\frac{x}{4})=\\lg 10+\\lg (\\frac{x}{4})$$;$$\\lg [\\frac{9}{2}(x-8)]=\\lg [10(\\frac{x}{4})]$$;$$ \\frac{ (9x)}{2}-36= \\frac{ (10x)}{4}= \\frac{ (5x)}{2}$$;$$2x=36$$;$$x=18$$ (ANS);b) $$9^{(2x)}+2(9^{(x+1)})=40$$;$$9^{(2x)}+2(9^x)(9)=40$$;$$9^{(2x)}+18(9^x)-40=0$$;;Let $$u=9^x$$;$$u^2+18u-40=0$$;$$(u+20)(u-2)=0$$;$$u=-20 or 2$$;$$9^x=-20(N.A) or 2$$;$$9^x=2$$;$$x\\lg 9=\\lg 2$$;$$x= \\frac{ (\\lg 2)}{(\\lg 9)}=0.315$$ (3 s.f) (ANS);c) $$y=e^x-e^{-x}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=e^x+e^{-x}$$;$$e^x>0$$ for all real x, and $$e^{-x}>0$$ for all real x as well.;Thus $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=e^x+e^{-x}>0$$ for all real x.;Hence y has no turning point s. ;Therefore the curve $$y=e^x-e^{-x}$$ has no turning point s (shown).;img;img;$$e^{2x}-1=3e^x$$;Divide by $$e^x$$,;$$e^x-e^{-x}=3$$;From the graphs, x = 1.20 (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (263,'199900104004','a) i) $$y=Ak^x$$;$$\\lg y=\\lg A+x\\lg k$$;$$\\lg y=x\\lg k+\\lg A$$ (ANS);$$Y=X(m)+c$$;Therefore A straight line can be drawn with lg  y as the vertical axis, x as the horizontal axis, lg  k as the gradient and lg  A as the vertical-axis intercept;ii;img; From the graph, vertical intercept $$\\approx 0.5$$, $$\\lg  A \\approx  0.5$$;$$A \\approx  31.6$$ (3s.f.) (ANS);;Gradient ;$$\\approx \\frac{ (2.35-0.5)}{(0.65-0)}$$;=$$ \\frac{1.85}{2.65}$$;$$\\lg  k\\approx \\frac{1.85}{2.65}$$;$$k\\approx 4.99$$ (3 s.f) (ANS);img;iii) $$y = 600$$;$$\\lg  y = 2.78$$;From the graph, ;$$x \\approx  3.25$$ (ANS);b) Gradient of graph = $$ \\frac{ (9-5)}{(5-3)}= \\frac{4}{2}=2$$;Equation of graph:;$$y^2=2x^2y+c$$;At (3, 5);5 = 2(3) + c;c = - 1;$$y^2=2x^2y-1$$;when $$x=\\frac{1}{2}\\sqrt 5$$;$$y^2=2(\\frac{1}{2} \\sqrt 5)^2y-1$$;=$$2(\\frac{5}{4})y-1$$;=$$ \\frac{5}{2}y-1$$;$$y^2- \\frac{5}{2}y+1=0$$;$$2y^2-5y+2=0$$;$$(y-2)(2y-1)=0$$;$$y=2 or \\frac{1}{2}$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (264,'199900104005','a) To show that $$4\\sin A\\cos ^3A-4\\cos A\\sin ^3A-=\\sin 4A$$;LHS = $$4\\sin A\\cos ^3A-4\\cos A\\sin ^3A$$;=$$2\\sin 2A\\cos ^2A-2\\sin 2A\\sin ^2A$$;=$$2\\sin 2A(\\cos ^2A-\\sin ^2A)$$;=$$2\\sin 2A\\cos 2A$$;=$$\\sin 4A$$ ;=RHS (shown);b)i) Let T be the foot of the perpendicular line from C to AB;$$\\sin \\theta = \\frac{ (TC)}{(15)}$$;$$TC=15\\sin \\theta $$;$$AD=TC=15\\sin \\theta $$ (ANS);$$\\cos \\theta = \\frac{ (TB)}{(15)}$$;$$TB=15\\cos \\theta $$;$$DC=AB-TB=10-15\\cos \\theta $$ (ANS);ii) Perimeter = 45 cm;$$10+15+(10-15\\cos \\theta )+15\\sin \\theta =45$$;$$15\\sin \\theta -15\\cos \\theta =10$$;$$3(\\sin \\theta -\\cos \\theta )=2$$;$$\\sin \\theta -\\cos \\theta = \\frac{2}{3}$$;Let $$\\sin \\theta -\\cos \\theta =A\\sin (\\theta -\\alpha )$$;Then $$\\sin \\theta -\\cos \\theta =A\\sin \\theta \\cos \\alpha -A\\cos \\theta \\sin \\alpha $$;$$A\\sin \\alpha =1$$;$$A\\cos \\alpha =1$$;$$A=\\sqrt {1^2+1^2}=\\sqrt 2$$;$$\\alpha =\\tan ^{-1}(1)=45^{\\circ}$$;Hence;$$\\sin \\theta -\\cos \\theta =\\sqrt 2\\sin (\\theta -45^{\\circ})= \\frac{2}{3}$$;$$\\theta -45^{\\circ}=\\sin ^{-1}( \\frac{\\sqrt 2}{3})$$;$$\\theta -45^{\\circ}=28.13^{\\circ}$$;$$\\theta =73.13^{\\circ}$$ (ANS);c)$$ \\frac{\\sin (A-B)}{(\\sin (A+B))}=2$$;$$ \\frac{ (\\sin A\\cos B-\\cos A\\sin B)}{(\\sin A\\cos B+\\cos A\\sin B)}=2$$;$$\\sin A\\cos B-\\cos A\\sin B=2\\sin A\\cos B+2\\cos A\\sin B$$;$$-\\sin A\\cos B=3\\cos A\\sin B$$;$$ \\frac{\\sin A}{\\cos A}\\ast \\frac{\\cos B}{\\sin B}=-3$$;$$\\tan A\\cot B=-3$$ (ANS)');
INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (265,'199900104006','a) $$y=x\\cos x$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=x(-\\sin x)+(1)\\cos x$$;=$$\\cos x-x\\sin x$$;When x = 0.5,;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\cos (0.5)-(0.5)\\sin (0.5)$$;=0.64(to 2 d.p) (ANS);b)$$y=\\sqrt {x^2-6x+25}$$;=$$(x^2-6x+25)^{(\\frac{1}{2})}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=\\frac{1}{2}(x^2-6x+25)^{-\\frac{1}{2}}(2x-6)$$;=$$ \\frac{ (x-3)}{(\\sqrt {x^2-6x+25})}$$;At (0, 5),;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}= \\frac{ (0-3)}{(\\sqrt {0^2-6(0)+25})}=- \\frac{3}{5}$$;Equation of tangent: ;$$y=- \\frac{3}{5}x+5$$ (ANS);c)$$y= \\frac{ (7x-2)}{(2x+3)}$$, where $$x\\neq-1.5$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}= \\frac{ (7(2x+3)-2(7x-2))}{(2x+3)^2}$$;=$$ \\frac{ (14+21-14x+4)}{(2x+3)^2}$$;=$$ \\frac{25}{(2x+3)^2}, x\\neq -1.5$$;since $$(2x+3)^2$$ is always positive, $$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}$$ is also always positive(shown).;$$\\delta y\\approx \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}\\ast \\delta x$$;when x = 36,;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}= \\frac{25}{(2(36)+3)^2}=\\frac{1}{2}25$$;$$\\delta x=0.045$$;$$\\delta y\\approx \\frac{1}{2}25(0.045)$$;=$$2\\times  10^{-4}$$ (ANS);$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} t}=4\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} y} \\ast  \\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}=4\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} t}$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} x}{\\mathrm{d} y}=4$$;$$ \\frac{ (2x+3)^2}{25}=4$$;$$(2x+3)^2=100$$;$$2x+3= \\pm 10$$;$$x= \\frac{ (\\pm 10-3)}{2}$$;=$$3 \\frac{1}{2} or -6 \\frac{1}{2}$$ (ANS)');
