INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (344,'200100102007','a) i) $$3\\sin x+2\\cos x-=R\\sin (x+\\alpha )-=R\\sin x\\cos \\alpha +R\\cos x\\sin \\alpha $$;$$R\\cos \\alpha =3$$ …..(1);$$R\\sin \\alpha =2$$ ……(2);$$R=\\sqrt {3^2+2^2}=\\sqrt {13}$$;$$\\tan \\alpha =\\frac{2}{3}$$;$$\\alpha =0.588$$;$$3\\sin x+2\\cos x-=\\sqrt {13}(x+0.588)$$ (ANS);ii)$$-1\\leq \\sin (x+0.588)\\leq 1$$;Therefore Maximum value of $$\\sqrt {13}(x+0.588)$$ is $$\\sqrt {13}$$;This will occur when ;$$(x+0.588)= \\frac{\\pi }{2}$$;$$x= \\frac{\\pi }{2}-0.588=0.983$$;Therefore P(0.983, 3.61) (ANS);iii)(k, 1) is a point  on the curve  y = 3 \\sin  x + 2 \\cos  x;$$\\sqrt {13}(k+0.588)=1$$;$$\\sin (k+0.588)= \\frac{1}{\\sqrt {13}}$$;$$k+0.588=0.281,2.86$$;$$k=-0.307(rej),2.272$$ (ANS);b)$$8\\cos x\\cos ^3x$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=8\\sin x(3\\cos ^2x)(-\\sin x)+\\cos ^3x(8\\cos x)$$;=$$-24\\sin ^2x\\cos ^2x+8\\cos ^4x$$;=$$8\\cos ^2x(-3\\sin ^2x+\\cos ^2x)$$;=$$8\\cos ^2x(-3+3\\cos ^2x+\\cos ^2x)$$;=$$8\\cos ^2x(4\\cos ^2x-3)$$ (ANS);$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=0$$;$$8\\cos ^2x(4\\cos ^2x-3)=0$$;$$\\cos ^2x=0 or \\cos ^2x=\\frac{3}{4}$$;$$\\cos x=0 or \\cos x=\\pm \\sqrt {\\frac{3}{2}}$$;$$since 0<x< \\frac{\\pi }{2},\\cos x=\\sqrt {\\frac{3}{2}}$$;$$x= \\frac{\\pi }{6}\\Rightarrow y=2.60$$ ;Therefore $$( \\frac{\\pi }{6}, 2.60)$$ (ANS)');
