INSERT INTO `DBManagement_answer` (`id`,`question_id_id`,`content`) VALUES (358,'200100103012','a) $$y=x^2-3x-3$$;$$\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=2x-3$$;$$x=2,\\frac{\\mathrm{d} y}{\\mathrm{d} x}=2(2)-3=1$$;Therefore gradient of curve at P is 1;since AB is parallel to the tangent at P,;Gradient of AB is 1;Equation of AB: ;y - 7 = 1(x - 5) (ANS);y = x + 2;since line AB meets curve at B, solve the 2 equations simul\\tan eously:;$$y=x+2$$ ………...(1);$$y=x^2-3x-3$$ …..(2);Sub (1) into (2):;$$x+2=x^2-3x-3$$;$$x^2-4x-5=0$$;$$(x+1)(x-5)=0$$;x = -1, x = 5;x = -1, y = -1 + 2 = 1;Therefore B(- 1, 1) (ANS);b) Let R be (2, a) and Q be (2, b);since R lies on line AB;a = 2 + 2 = 4;Therefore R = (2, 4) (ANS);Gradient of AC = $$ \\frac{ (7-(-3))}{(5-0)}=2$$;Equation of AC:;y - 7 = 2 (x - 5);y = 2x - 3;since Q lies on line AC:;b = 2(2) - 3= 1;Therefore Q is (2, 1) (ANS);c)$$ \\frac{ (CQ)}{(CA)}=\\frac{2}{5}$$;Therefore CQ:QA = 2 : 3 (ANS);d)Area of triangle ARQ ;=$$\\frac{1}{2}|(5,2,2,5),(7,4,1,7)|$$;=$$\\frac{1}{2}[(20+2+14)-(14+8+5)]$$;=$$\\frac{1}{2}(9)$$;=$$4.5 units^2$$ (ANS)');
